---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { format } from "date-fns";

const lastUpdated = new Date("2026-06-14");
---

<Layout
  title="Now"
  description="What I'm doing now — a snapshot of my current focus and activities."
  url="https://ekel.dev/now"
  ogImage="now.png"
>
  <div
    class:list={[
      "flex w-full flex-col items-start justify-start  mx-auto",
      "md:text-start",
    ]}
  >
    <section class="w-full mt-8">
      <h1
        class="mb-4 mt-0 text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-foreground"
      >
        Now
      </h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground text-lg sm:text-xl mb-0">
        Last updated: {format(lastUpdated, "MMMM d, yyyy")}
      </p>
    </section>

    <div
      class="flex w-full flex-col mt-10 sm:mt-16 items-start justify-start space-y-10"
    >
      <section class="w-full slide-enter-content">
        <h2
          class="mb-6 sm:mb-8 mt-0 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground"
        >
          Work
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mb-0 text-base sm:text-lg text-foreground leading-7 sm:leading-relaxed"
        >
          I'm working as a Web Programmer (Basically Fullstack Web Developer
          that also do DevOps stuff). Main stack: Typescript, Go, Docker.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="w-full slide-enter-content">
        <h2
          class="mb-6 sm:mb-8 mt-0 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground"
        >
          Learning
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mb-6 text-base sm:text-lg text-foreground leading-7 sm:leading-relaxed"
        >
          Deep dive into Go, DevOps, also how to deal and manage people.
          Occasionally reading about personal finance and (only) investing on
          sharia stock. For stock market, I'm interested in fundamental
          analysis, corporate action, big money movement, and market sentiment.
          There are some quotes that I like:
        </p>
        <blockquote
          class="border-l-2 border-border/70 pl-6 my-6 italic text-base sm:text-lg text-muted-foreground"
        >
          "Be fearful when others are greedy, and greedy when others are
          fearful" — Warren Buffett
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote
          class="border-l-2 border-border/70 pl-6 my-6 italic text-base sm:text-lg text-muted-foreground"
        >
          "Risk is what you pay for opportunity" — Andry Hakim
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <section class="w-full slide-enter-content">
        <h2
          class="mb-6 sm:mb-8 mt-0 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground"
        >
          Reading
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mb-0 text-base sm:text-lg text-foreground leading-7 sm:leading-relaxed"
        >
          Currently reading <strong class="text-foreground font-medium"
            >Ini Koding</strong
          > by Hilman Ramadhan and <strong class="text-foreground font-medium"
            >Make Time</strong
          > by Jake Knapp & John Zeratsky.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="w-full slide-enter-content">
        <h2
          class="mb-6 sm:mb-8 mt-0 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground"
        >
          Playlist
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mb-0 text-base sm:text-lg text-foreground leading-7 sm:leading-relaxed"
        >
          I don't have any music playlist because my music taste is random. Also
          I rarely listen to music. But I have a <a
            href="https://music.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLcauesmgnpZ9BBTEFyotPzX9MotTEVdKx&si=DCSEaL1jMkeidZ79"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="Murottal Playlist (opens in new tab)"
            class="text-foreground font-medium hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors"
            >Murottal Playlist</a
          > that updated regularly and always listen to it when I'm working or do
          something that require focus.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="w-full slide-enter-content">
        <h2
          class="mb-6 sm:mb-8 mt-0 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground"
        >
          Stuff
        </h2>
        <p
          class="mb-6 text-base sm:text-lg text-foreground leading-7 sm:leading-relaxed"
        >
          Well, outside of my interest in tech and finance, I also love to take
          care of my <a
            href="https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yamaha_Jupiter_MX"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="Yamaha Jupiter MX (opens in new tab)"
            class="text-foreground font-medium hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors"
            >2014-motorcycle</a
          > and do some modifications to it. Here are some modifications that I've
          done:
        </p>
        <ul
          role="list"
          class="space-y-3 text-base sm:text-lg text-foreground list-none pl-0"
        >
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span
              class="absolute left-0 top-2.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
            ></span>(Oil filter, air filter, spark plug header) using Daytona.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span
              class="absolute left-0 top-2.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
            ></span>(Spark plug) using NGK Iridium.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span
              class="absolute left-0 top-2.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
            ></span>(Velg) using BRT Chemco.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span
              class="absolute left-0 top-2.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
            ></span>(Side-view Mirror) using parts from Yamaha 125Z.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span
              class="absolute left-0 top-2.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
            ></span>(Tire profile) 80/80-17 front, 90/80-17 rear.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span
              class="absolute left-0 top-2.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
            ></span>(Seat) using latex foam + custom seat cover.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
